 Project Structure: User Experience & Page Architecture

From a research participant's perspective, the platform is structured as a "Linear Experimental Funnel." This ensures that data collectionâ€”from the initial consent to the final usability surveyâ€”follows a controlled, logical path[cite: 141, 151].

 1. Landing & Consent Page (The Entry)
    - Informational: Displays the research title, purpose of the study, and the Department of Cyber Security branding[cite: 424, 425].
    - Functional: Contains the Participant Consent Form[cite: 423, 435]. The user must check the "Agree" boxes to proceed to the testing environment[cite: 435, 436].

 2. Pathway Selection (The Router)
    - Informational: Briefly explains that the user will perform two different login tasks[cite: 428, 429].
    - Functional: Uses an A/B Testing module to assign the user to "Sequence A" (Traditional first) or "Sequence B" (Sovereign first) to prevent order bias[cite: 151].

 3. The Authentication Interface (The Core Test)
This page holds the "Dual-Stack" logic and changes its UI based on the active pathway[cite: 302, 341].

 Pathway A: Traditional Login
    - Informational: Standard fields for Username and Password[cite: 222, 260].
    - Functional: Captures keystroke timing and credential verification against the PostgreSQL database[cite: 257, 260].

 Pathway B: Sovereign Login (Your Custom Extension)
    - Informational: Visual cues for "Connect Wallet" and "Sign Message"[cite: 251, 326].
    - Functional: Interfaces with your browser extension provider to perform the ECDSA challenge-response handshake[cite: 224, 326].



 4. Post-Login Student Dashboard (Verification)
    - Informational: Confirms successful authentication with a "Welcome, [User]" message and displays session metadata (e.g., Auth Method used)[cite: 254, 359].
    - Functional: Holds the "Complete Task" button which signals the end of the timed telemetry session[cite: 371].

 5. Usability Evaluation Page (The Result)
    - Informational: Presents the 5-point Likert Scale questions[cite: 405].
    - Functional: Collects qualitative data on Perceived Ease of Use and Perceived Security[cite: 406, 411]. Upon submission, the "Admin Reset Protocol" triggers to clear all session data for the next user[cite: 266, 418].


